rget tradeskills. You'll sink a lot of time and money into them and probably never make a profit. Lowest risk is probably tailoring though, don't have to spend as much money as other skills and can make most of your money back later on with 10-slot backpacks.<P>High Elf is good for any trade skill (other than Tinkering or Alchemy) because of high INT and our naturally good looks that cause women to swoon, shopkeepers to sell components to you cheap, and customers to buy your goods.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aquinas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">As far as I can tell, the only trade skill that "works" economically is jewelcrafting.  However, it takes a very large investment to get your skill up to the point where you can make the popular items.  It's also inconvenient to do if you're not an enchanter, as you'll need to get an enchanter to enchant your components.<P>If you're just looking at tradeskills as a source of income, I'd just forget it and focus on hunting.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Panteroo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My advice on tradeskills is that if your not doing it for a reason (i.e. being your guilds blacksmith for example) you will find that they are not profitable.. not only in terms of money spent, but also time invested.<P>Here is a little rundown of how i see things:<P><b>Blacksmithing</b>: Sounds really cool, infact i have a blacksmithing skill of 177... And you can get to the level of creating FS Plate armor for about 700-1000pp. However, unless your on a newer server, the market for FS is horribly low. High Elf cultural armor looks really cool ! unfortunately, you need uber-blue diamonds to enchant the ore (sell for 2.5kpp on Fennin Ro) AND 2 Essense of Moonlight (very rare drop off vampires in MM and dread wolves in Kithacor) AND Vial of Swirling Mists (very rare drop off 