nt and you wanna make it for yourself.<p>[This message has been edited by Aean (edited 03-21-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trilvan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">While I agree there is also the imbued feild breast plate of erollisi marr which the gem only costs about 1 plat for and I would deffintly pay the 1300 plat for one. <BR>What it comes down to with smithing the cultural armour is which gem/gems are for your race some is actualy worth doing others no way.<P>------------------<BR>Trilvan Lostheart<BR>46th Cleric of Love Peace and Happiness</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not to mention it's such a pain to raise your skill (smithing).  I was interested in doing the smithing when they first introduced the cultural armor.  <P>I raised my skill to 175 and then went out and made the long boring trek from FP to HP to get Medium quality sheets to make fine plate.<P>After doing that a few dozen times and managing to get my skill to 187, I decided it just wasn't worth my time and effort.<P>If they would have made it more viable to do by putting materials in each city, then maybe it might be worth doing.<P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>59th Dwarven Templar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would love to make fine steel for people but there are two main things 1 is that stinkin leather padding, WHY do we have to go out and get that stuff? you'd figure the leather shops would have learned to make it by now.:P and 2 is the cost. People do pay for it but not many. really this armour is supposed to be the halfway point bewteen bronze armour and our quest armours. The stuff is so expensive to buy that you can actually just buy most of your quest armours for the same prices, not all of it mind you but a fair amount of it you can. <P>think about it this way, how much would you pay for a 19ac breastplate? a 15 ac BP is 15 plat, and 17 ac BP is 34 plat so if we follow that pattern a Fine Steel BP should cost around 76plat if we were to double it. hell even for 100 it would be worth it but 300??? hell no. Personally i would stick with the 2 less ac breastplate until I could get my quest one and spend my money on better things like jewelry. but then again what do I know, i just play the game:/</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
